74 /* In GLEW_REGAL mode we call direcly into the linked
75  libRegal.so glGetProcAddressREGAL for looking up
76  the GL function pointers. */
77 
78 # undef glGetProcAddressREGAL

80 extern void * __stdcall glGetProcAddressREGAL(const GLchar *name);
81 static void * (__stdcall * regalGetProcAddress) (const GLchar *) = glGetProcAddressREGAL;
82 # else
83 extern void * glGetProcAddressREGAL(const GLchar *name);
84 static void * (*regalGetProcAddress) (const GLchar *) = glGetProcAddressREGAL;
85 # endif
86 # define glGetProcAddressREGAL GLEW_GET_FUN(__glewGetProcAddressREGAL)

93 void* dlGetProcAddress (const GLubyte* name)
94 {
95  static void* h = NULL;
96  static void* gpa;
97 
98  if (h == NULL)
99  {
100  if ((h = dlopen(NULL, RTLD_LAZY | RTLD_LOCAL)) == NULL) return NULL;
101  gpa = dlsym(h, "glXGetProcAddress");
102  }
103 
104  if (gpa != NULL)
105  return ((void*(*)(const GLubyte*))gpa)(name);
106  else
107  return dlsym(h, (const char*)name);
108 }
109 #endif /* __sgi || __sun || GLEW_APPLE_GLX */
110 
111 #if defined(__APPLE__)
112 #include <stdlib.h>
113 #include <string.h>
114 #include <AvailabilityMacros.h>
115 
116 #ifdef MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_3
117 
118 #include <dlfcn.h>
119 
120 void* NSGLGetProcAddress (const GLubyte *name)
121 {
122  static void* image = NULL;
123  void* addr;
124  if (NULL == image)
125  {
126  image = dlopen("/System/Library/Frameworks/OpenGL.framework/Versions/Current/OpenGL", RTLD_LAZY);
127  }
128  if( !image ) return NULL;
129  addr = dlsym(image, (const char*)name);
130  if( addr ) return addr;
131 #ifdef GLEW_APPLE_GLX
132  return dlGetProcAddress( name ); // try next for glx symbols
133 #else
134  return NULL;
135 #endif
136 }
137 #else
138 
139 #include <mach-o/dyld.h>
140 
141 void* NSGLGetProcAddress (const GLubyte *name)
142 {
143  static const struct mach_header* image = NULL;
144  NSSymbol symbol;
145  char* symbolName;
146  if (NULL == image)
147  {
148  image = NSAddImage("/System/Library/Frameworks/OpenGL.framework/Versions/Current/OpenGL", NSADDIMAGE_OPTION_RETURN_ON_ERROR);
149  }
150  /* prepend a '_' for the Unix C symbol mangling convention */
151  symbolName = malloc(strlen((const char*)name) + 2);
152  strcpy(symbolName+1, (const char*)name);
153  symbolName[0] = '_';
154  symbol = NULL;
155  /* if (NSIsSymbolNameDefined(symbolName))
156  symbol = NSLookupAndBindSymbol(symbolName); */
157  symbol = image ? NSLookupSymbolInImage(image, symbolName, NSLOOKUPSYMBOLINIMAGE_OPTION_BIND | NSLOOKUPSYMBOLINIMAGE_OPTION_RETURN_ON_ERROR) : NULL;
158  free(symbolName);
159  if( symbol ) return NSAddressOfSymbol(symbol);
160 #ifdef GLEW_APPLE_GLX
161  return dlGetProcAddress( name ); // try next for glx symbols
162 #else
163  return NULL;
164 #endif
165 }
166 #endif /* MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_3 */
167 #endif /* __APPLE__ */
168 
169 /*
170  * Define glewGetProcAddress.
171  */
172 #if defined(GLEW_REGAL)
173 # define glewGetProcAddress(name) regalGetProcAddress((const GLchar *) name)
174 #elif defined(_WIN32)
175 # define glewGetProcAddress(name) wglGetProcAddress((LPCSTR)name)
176 #elif defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(GLEW_APPLE_GLX)
177 # define glewGetProcAddress(name) NSGLGetProcAddress(name)
178 #elif defined(__sgi) || defined(__sun) || defined(__HAIKU__)
179 # define glewGetProcAddress(name) dlGetProcAddress(name)
180 #elif defined(__ANDROID__)
181 # define glewGetProcAddress(name) NULL /* TODO */
182 #elif defined(__native_client__)
183 # define glewGetProcAddress(name) NULL /* TODO */
184 #else /* __linux */
185 # define glewGetProcAddress(name) (*glXGetProcAddressARB)(name)
186 #endif

217 /*
218  * GLEW, just like OpenGL or GLU, does not rely on the standard C library.
219  * These functions implement the functionality required in this file.
220  */
221 static GLuint _glewStrLen (const GLubyte* s)
222 {
223  GLuint i=0;
224  if (s == NULL) return 0;
225  while (s[i] != '\0') i++;
226  return i;
227 }
228 
229 static GLuint _glewStrCLen (const GLubyte* s, GLubyte c)
230 {
231  GLuint i=0;
232  if (s == NULL) return 0;
233  while (s[i] != '\0' && s[i] != c) i++;
234  return (s[i] == '\0' || s[i] == c) ? i : 0;
235 }
236 
237 static GLboolean _glewStrSame (const GLubyte* a, const GLubyte* b, GLuint n)
238 {
239  GLuint i=0;
240  if(a == NULL || b == NULL)
241  return (a == NULL && b == NULL && n == 0) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
242  while (i < n && a[i] != '\0' && b[i] != '\0' && a[i] == b[i]) i++;
243  return i == n ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
244 }
245 
246 static GLboolean _glewStrSame1 (const GLubyte** a, GLuint* na, const GLubyte* b, GLuint nb)
247 {
248  while (*na > 0 && (**a == ' ' || **a == '\n' || **a == '\r' || **a == '\t'))
249  {
250  (*a)++;
251  (*na)--;
252  }
253  if(*na >= nb)
254  {
255  GLuint i=0;
256  while (i < nb && (*a)+i != NULL && b+i != NULL && (*a)[i] == b[i]) i++;
257  if(i == nb)
258  {
259  *a = *a + nb;
260  *na = *na - nb;
261  return GL_TRUE;
262  }
263  }
264  return GL_FALSE;
265 }
266 
267 static GLboolean _glewStrSame2 (const GLubyte** a, GLuint* na, const GLubyte* b, GLuint nb)
268 {
269  if(*na >= nb)
270  {
271  GLuint i=0;
272  while (i < nb && (*a)+i != NULL && b+i != NULL && (*a)[i] == b[i]) i++;
273  if(i == nb)
274  {
275  *a = *a + nb;
276  *na = *na - nb;
277  return GL_TRUE;
278  }
279  }
280  return GL_FALSE;
281 }
282 
283 static GLboolean _glewStrSame3 (const GLubyte** a, GLuint* na, const GLubyte* b, GLuint nb)
284 {
285  if(*na >= nb)
286  {
287  GLuint i=0;
288  while (i < nb && (*a)+i != NULL && b+i != NULL && (*a)[i] == b[i]) i++;
289  if (i == nb && (*na == nb || (*a)[i] == ' ' || (*a)[i] == '\n' || (*a)[i] == '\r' || (*a)[i] == '\t'))
290  {
291  *a = *a + nb;
292  *na = *na - nb;
293  return GL_TRUE;
294  }
295  }
296  return GL_FALSE;
297 }
298 
299 /*
300  * Search for name in the extensions string. Use of strstr()
301  * is not sufficient because extension names can be prefixes of
302  * other extension names. Could use strtok() but the constant
303  * string returned by glGetString might be in read-only memory.
304  */
305 static GLboolean _glewSearchExtension (const char* name, const GLubyte *start, const GLubyte *end)
306 {
307  const GLubyte* p;
308  GLuint len = _glewStrLen((const GLubyte*)name);
309  p = start;
310  while (p < end)
311  {
312  GLuint n = _glewStrCLen(p, ' ');
313  if (len == n && _glewStrSame((const GLubyte*)name, p, n)) return GL_TRUE;
314  p += n+1;
315  }
316  return GL_FALSE;
317 }

10267 GLboolean GLEWAPIENTRY glewGetExtension (const char* name)
10268 {
10269  const GLubyte* start;
10270  const GLubyte* end;
10271  start = (const GLubyte*)glGetString(GL_EXTENSIONS);
10272  if (start == 0)
10273  return GL_FALSE;
10274  end = start + _glewStrLen(start);
10275  return _glewSearchExtension(name, start, end);
10276 }

10283 GLenum GLEWAPIENTRY glewContextInit (GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_DEF_LIST)
10284 {
10285  const GLubyte* s;
10286  GLuint dot;
10287  GLint major, minor;
10288  const GLubyte* extStart;
10289  const GLubyte* extEnd;
10290  /* query opengl version */
10291  s = glGetString(GL_VERSION);
10292  dot = _glewStrCLen(s, '.');
10293  if (dot == 0)
10294  return GLEW_ERROR_NO_GL_VERSION;
10295 
10296  major = s[dot-1]-'0';
10297  minor = s[dot+1]-'0';
10298 
10299  if (minor < 0 || minor > 9)
10300  minor = 0;
10301  if (major<0 || major>9)
10302  return GLEW_ERROR_NO_GL_VERSION;
10303 
10304 
10305  if (major == 1 && minor == 0)
10306  {
10307  return GLEW_ERROR_GL_VERSION_10_ONLY;
10308  }
10309  else
10310  {
10311  GLEW_VERSION_4_5 = ( major > 4 ) || ( major == 4 && minor >= 5 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10312  GLEW_VERSION_4_4 = GLEW_VERSION_4_5 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 4 && minor >= 4 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10313  GLEW_VERSION_4_3 = GLEW_VERSION_4_4 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 4 && minor >= 3 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10314  GLEW_VERSION_4_2 = GLEW_VERSION_4_3 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 4 && minor >= 2 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10315  GLEW_VERSION_4_1 = GLEW_VERSION_4_2 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 4 && minor >= 1 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10316  GLEW_VERSION_4_0 = GLEW_VERSION_4_1 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 4 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10317  GLEW_VERSION_3_3 = GLEW_VERSION_4_0 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 3 && minor >= 3 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10318  GLEW_VERSION_3_2 = GLEW_VERSION_3_3 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 3 && minor >= 2 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10319  GLEW_VERSION_3_1 = GLEW_VERSION_3_2 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 3 && minor >= 1 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;

10321  GLEW_VERSION_2_1 = GLEW_VERSION_3_0 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 2 && minor >= 1 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10322  GLEW_VERSION_2_0 = GLEW_VERSION_2_1 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 2 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10323  GLEW_VERSION_1_5 = GLEW_VERSION_2_0 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 1 && minor >= 5 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;

10326  GLEW_VERSION_1_2_1 = GLEW_VERSION_1_3 == GL_TRUE ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10327  GLEW_VERSION_1_2 = GLEW_VERSION_1_2_1 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 1 && minor >= 2 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
10328  GLEW_VERSION_1_1 = GLEW_VERSION_1_2 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 1 && minor >= 1 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;

13093 
13094 static PFNWGLGETEXTENSIONSSTRINGARBPROC _wglewGetExtensionsStringARB = NULL;
13095 static PFNWGLGETEXTENSIONSSTRINGEXTPROC _wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT = NULL;
13096 
13097 GLboolean GLEWAPIENTRY wglewGetExtension (const char* name)
13098 {
13099  const GLubyte* start;
13100  const GLubyte* end;
13101  if (_wglewGetExtensionsStringARB == NULL)
13102  if (_wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT == NULL)
13103  return GL_FALSE;
13104  else
13105  start = (const GLubyte*)_wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT();
13106  else
13107  start = (const GLubyte*)_wglewGetExtensionsStringARB(wglGetCurrentDC());
13108  if (start == 0)
13109  return GL_FALSE;
13110  end = start + _glewStrLen(start);
13111  return _glewSearchExtension(name, start, end);
13112 }
13113 
13114 GLenum GLEWAPIENTRY wglewContextInit (WGLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_DEF_LIST)
13115 {
13116  GLboolean crippled;
13117  const GLubyte* extStart;
13118  const GLubyte* extEnd;
13119  /* find wgl extension string query functions */
13120  _wglewGetExtensionsStringARB = (PFNWGLGETEXTENSIONSSTRINGARBPROC)glewGetProcAddress((const GLubyte*)"wglGetExtensionsStringARB");
13121  _wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT = (PFNWGLGETEXTENSIONSSTRINGEXTPROC)glewGetProcAddress((const GLubyte*)"wglGetExtensionsStringEXT");
13122  /* query wgl extension string */
13123  if (_wglewGetExtensionsStringARB == NULL)
13124  if (_wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT == NULL)
13125  extStart = (const GLubyte*)"";
13126  else
13127  extStart = (const GLubyte*)_wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT();
13128  else
13129  extStart = (const GLubyte*)_wglewGetExtensionsStringARB(wglGetCurrentDC());
13130  extEnd = extStart + _glewStrLen(extStart);
13131  /* initialize extensions */
13132  crippled = _wglewGetExtensionsStringARB == NULL && _wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT == NULL;
13133 #ifdef WGL_3DFX_multisample
13134  WGLEW_3DFX_multisample = _glewSearchExtension("WGL_3DFX_multisample", extStart, extEnd);
13135 #endif /* WGL_3DFX_multisample */
13136 #ifdef WGL_3DL_stereo_control
13137  WGLEW_3DL_stereo_control = _glewSearchExtension("WGL_3DL_stereo_control", extStart, extEnd);
13138  if (glewExperimental || WGLEW_3DL_stereo_control|| crippled) WGLEW_3DL_stereo_control= !_glewInit_WGL_3DL_stereo_control(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
13139 #endif /* WGL_3DL_stereo_control */
13140 #ifdef WGL_AMD_gpu_association
13141  WGLEW_AMD_gpu_association = _glewSearchExtension("WGL_AMD_gpu_association", extStart, extEnd);
13142  if (glewExperimental || WGLEW_AMD_gpu_association|| crippled) WGLEW_AMD_gpu_association= !_glewInit_WGL_AMD_gpu_association(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
13143 #endif /* WGL_AMD_gpu_association */
13144 #ifdef WGL_ARB_buffer_region
13145  WGLEW_ARB_buffer_region = _glewSearchExtension("WGL_ARB_buffer_region", extStart, extEnd);
13146  if (glewExperimental || WGLEW_ARB_buffer_region|| crippled) WGLEW_ARB_buffer_region= !_glewInit_WGL_ARB_buffer_region(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);

14233 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------ */
14234 
14235 GLboolean glxewGetExtension (const char* name)
14236 {
14237  const GLubyte* start;
14238  const GLubyte* end;
14239 
14240  if (glXGetCurrentDisplay == NULL) return GL_FALSE;
14241  start = (const GLubyte*)glXGetClientString(glXGetCurrentDisplay(), GLX_EXTENSIONS);
14242  if (0 == start) return GL_FALSE;
14243  end = start + _glewStrLen(start);
14244  return _glewSearchExtension(name, start, end);
14245 }
14246 
14247 GLenum glxewContextInit (GLXEW_CONTEXT_ARG_DEF_LIST)
14248 {
14249  int major, minor;
14250  const GLubyte* extStart;
14251  const GLubyte* extEnd;
14252  /* initialize core GLX 1.2 */
14253  if (_glewInit_GLX_VERSION_1_2(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT)) return GLEW_ERROR_GLX_VERSION_11_ONLY;
14254  /* initialize flags */
14255  GLXEW_VERSION_1_0 = GL_TRUE;
14256  GLXEW_VERSION_1_1 = GL_TRUE;
14257  GLXEW_VERSION_1_2 = GL_TRUE;
14258  GLXEW_VERSION_1_3 = GL_TRUE;
14259  GLXEW_VERSION_1_4 = GL_TRUE;
14260  /* query GLX version */
14261  glXQueryVersion(glXGetCurrentDisplay(), &major, &minor);
14262  if (major == 1 && minor <= 3)
14263  {
14264  switch (minor)
14265  {
14266  case 3:
14267  GLXEW_VERSION_1_4 = GL_FALSE;
14268  break;
14269  case 2:
14270  GLXEW_VERSION_1_4 = GL_FALSE;
14271  GLXEW_VERSION_1_3 = GL_FALSE;
14272  break;
14273  default:
14274  return GLEW_ERROR_GLX_VERSION_11_ONLY;
14275  break;
14276  }
14277  }
14278  /* query GLX extension string */
14279  extStart = 0;
14280  if (glXGetCurrentDisplay != NULL)
14281  extStart = (const GLubyte*)glXGetClientString(glXGetCurrentDisplay(), GLX_EXTENSIONS);
14282  if (extStart == 0)
14283  extStart = (const GLubyte *)"";
14284  extEnd = extStart + _glewStrLen(extStart);
14285  /* initialize extensions */
14286 #ifdef GLX_VERSION_1_3
14287  if (glewExperimental || GLXEW_VERSION_1_3) GLXEW_VERSION_1_3 = !_glewInit_GLX_VERSION_1_3(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
14288 #endif /* GLX_VERSION_1_3 */
14289 #ifdef GLX_3DFX_multisample
14290  GLXEW_3DFX_multisample = _glewSearchExtension("GLX_3DFX_multisample", extStart, extEnd);
14291 #endif /* GLX_3DFX_multisample */
14292 #ifdef GLX_AMD_gpu_association
14293  GLXEW_AMD_gpu_association = _glewSearchExtension("GLX_AMD_gpu_association", extStart, extEnd);
14294  if (glewExperimental || GLXEW_AMD_gpu_association) GLXEW_AMD_gpu_association = !_glewInit_GLX_AMD_gpu_association(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
14295 #endif /* GLX_AMD_gpu_association */
14296 #ifdef GLX_ARB_context_flush_control
14297  GLXEW_ARB_context_flush_control = _glewSearchExtension("GLX_ARB_context_flush_control", extStart, extEnd);
14298 #endif /* GLX_ARB_context_flush_control */
14299 #ifdef GLX_ARB_create_context
14300  GLXEW_ARB_create_context = _glewSearchExtension("GLX_ARB_create_context", extStart, extEnd);
14301  if (glewExperimental || GLXEW_ARB_create_context) GLXEW_ARB_create_context = !_glewInit_GLX_ARB_create_context(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
14302 #endif /* GLX_ARB_create_context */
14303 #ifdef GLX_ARB_create_context_profile
14304  GLXEW_ARB_create_context_profile = _glewSearchExtension("GLX_ARB_create_context_profile", extStart, extEnd);
14305 #endif /* GLX_ARB_create_context_profile */
14306 #ifdef GLX_ARB_create_context_robustness

14526 const GLubyte * GLEWAPIENTRY glewGetErrorString (GLenum error)
14527 {
14528  static const GLubyte* _glewErrorString[] =
14529  {
14530  (const GLubyte*)"No error",
14531  (const GLubyte*)"Missing GL version",
14532  (const GLubyte*)"GL 1.1 and up are not supported",
14533  (const GLubyte*)"GLX 1.2 and up are not supported",
14534  (const GLubyte*)"Unknown error"
14535  };
14536  const size_t max_error = sizeof(_glewErrorString)/sizeof(*_glewErrorString) - 1;
14537  return _glewErrorString[(size_t)error > max_error ? max_error : (size_t)error];
14538 }
14539 
14540 const GLubyte * GLEWAPIENTRY glewGetString (GLenum name)
14541 {
14542  static const GLubyte* _glewString[] =
14543  {
14544  (const GLubyte*)NULL,
14545  (const GLubyte*)"1.12.0",
14546  (const GLubyte*)"1",
14547  (const GLubyte*)"12",
14548  (const GLubyte*)"0"
14549  };
14550  const size_t max_string = sizeof(_glewString)/sizeof(*_glewString) - 1;
14551  return _glewString[(size_t)name > max_string ? 0 : (size_t)name];
14552 }

14560 #if defined(_WIN32)
14561 extern GLenum GLEWAPIENTRY wglewContextInit (void);
14562 #elif !defined(__ANDROID__) && !defined(__native_client__) && !defined(__HAIKU__) && (!defined(__APPLE__) || defined(GLEW_APPLE_GLX))
14563 extern GLenum GLEWAPIENTRY glxewContextInit (void);
14564 #endif /* _WIN32 */
14565 
14566 GLenum GLEWAPIENTRY glewInit (void)
14567 {
14568  GLenum r;
14569  r = glewContextInit();
14570  if ( r != 0 ) return r;
14571 #if defined(_WIN32)
14572  return wglewContextInit();
14573 #elif !defined(__ANDROID__) && !defined(__native_client__) && !defined(__HAIKU__) && (!defined(__APPLE__) || defined(GLEW_APPLE_GLX)) /* _UNIX */
14574  return glxewContextInit();
14575 #else
14576  return r;
14577 #endif /* _WIN32 */
14578 }
14579 
14580 #endif /* !GLEW_MX */
14581 #ifdef GLEW_MX
14582 GLboolean GLEWAPIENTRY glewContextIsSupported (const GLEWContext* ctx, const char* name)
14583 #else
14584 GLboolean GLEWAPIENTRY glewIsSupported (const char* name)
14585 #endif
14586 {
14587  const GLubyte* pos = (const GLubyte*)name;
14588  GLuint len = _glewStrLen(pos);
14589  GLboolean ret = GL_TRUE;
14590  while (ret && len > 0)
14591  {
14592  if (_glewStrSame1(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"GL_", 3))
14593  {
14594  if (_glewStrSame2(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"VERSION_", 8))
14595  {
14596 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_2
14597  if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"1_2", 3))

14600  continue;
14601  }
14602 #endif
14603 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_2_1
14604  if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"1_2_1", 5))
14605  {
14606  ret = GLEW_VERSION_1_2_1;
14607  continue;
14608  }
14609 #endif
14610 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_3
14611  if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"1_3", 3))
14612  {
14613  ret = GLEW_VERSION_1_3;
14614  continue;
14615  }
14616 #endif
14617 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_4
14618  if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"1_4", 3))

14621  continue;
14622  }
14623 #endif
14624 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_5
